annotationA: Seryl-tRNA synthetase, mitochondrial (SerRS-m) catalyses the aminoacylation of tRNAser with serine, to be used for gene translation during protein synthesis
annotationB: Arginyl-tRNA synthetase, mitochondrial, isoform A; ATP binding; arginine-tRNA ligase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: arginyl-tRNA aminoacylation; Belongs to the class-I aminoacyl-tRNA synthetase family
